'''Heavenly Sounds''' is an ongoing concert series that presents contemporary secular music in churches and cathedrals around [[Australia]]. It is co-presented by artist management company One Louder and booking agency Artist Voice.

The first tour took place in November/December 2011 and featured Australian indie folk supergroup [[Seeker Lover Keeper]] (featuring [[Sarah Blasko]], [[Holly Throsby]] and [[Sally Seltmann]]), with opening acts Henry Wagons and Laura Jean<ref name="shm">{{cite web|author=Sarah Whyte |url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/sacred-venues-the-holy-grail-for-musicians-20120211-1sygy.html |title=Sacred venues the holy grail for musicians |publisher=Smh.com.au |date=2012-02-14 |accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref> Shows took place in [[Brisbane]], [[Sydney]], [[Newcastle, New South Wales|Newcastle]], [[Canberra]], [[Melbourne]], [[Hobart]], [[Perth]] and [[Adelaide]].

The second tour was in June 2012 and featured [[Lisa Mitchell]] and Georgia Fair who performed in Newcastle, Sydney, Brisbane, Melbourne, Adelaide and Perth.<ref name="abc">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/musicnews/s3464543.htm |title=Lisa Mitchell premieres 'Spiritus', announces church tour &#124; music news &#124; triple j |publisher=Abc.net.au |date=2012-03-27 |accessdate=2013-10-26}}</ref>

Subsequent tours have included [[Julia Stone]], [[The Civil Wars]], [[Beth Orton]], [[Michael Kiwanuka]], [[Kate Miller-Heidke]], [[Laura Marling]], and [[Sarah Blasko]]  The event co-directors Bill Cullen and Brett Murrihy created the Heavenly Sounds concept to offer something unique to both artists and audiences.<ref name="themusicnetwork">{{cite web|url=http://www.themusicnetwork.com/music-features/industry/2011/10/20/the-hot-seat-bill-cullen-and-brett-murrihy/ |accessdate=May 31, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618121025/http://www.themusicnetwork.com/music-features/industry/2011/10/20/the-hot-seat-bill-cullen-and-brett-murrihy |archivedate=June 18, 2012 }}</ref>

