 Island|Pagan]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060901131625/http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=0804-17=&volpage=erupt&format=expanded#E1981515]</ref> || 1981 || || |- ! style="background:#f60;"|5 | [[El Chichón]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041119092109/http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=1401-12=&volpage=erupt&format=expanded#E1982328]</ref> || 1982 || 3,500 || Ejected 7 million metric tons of sulfur dioxide into the stratosphere.<ref>{{Citation | last=Robock | first=Alan | title=Volcanic eruption, El Chichon | journal=The Earth system: physical and chemical dimensions of global environment change |publisher= John Wiley & Sons Ltd. Chichester | volume=1 | issue= | year=2002 | page=736 | url=http://climate.envsci.rutgers.edu/pdf/EGECElChichon.pdf }}</ref> |- ! style="background:#f90;"|4 | [[Galunggung]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060901124231/http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=0603-14=&volpage=erupt&format=expanded#E198245]</ref> || 1982 || || Notable for bringing attention to the dangers of volcanic ash on aircraft after two [[Boeing 747]] jets suffered engine failure from its ash cloud. |- ! style="background:#f90;"|4 | [[Colo (volcano)|Colo]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20041103094758/http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=0606-01=&volpage=erupt&format=expanded#E1983718]</ref> || 1983 || || |- ! style="background:#fc0;"|3 | [[Nevado del Ruiz]] || 1985 || 23,000 || [[Armero tragedy]] |- ! style="background:#f90;"|4 | [[Mount Augustine]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060901124256/http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=1103-01-&volpage=erupt&format=expanded#E1986327]</ref> || 1986 || || |- ! style="background:#f90;"|4 | [[Chikurachki]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060901122749/http://www.volcano.si.edu/world/volcano.cfm?vnum=0900-36=&volpage=erupt&format=expanded#E19861118]</ref> || 1986 || || |- ! style="background:#f90;"|4 | [[Kliuchevskoi]]<ref>[https://web.archive.org